### Issue 2: Widget Silently Disappears If `#cab-promo-banner` Never Exists (Lines 228–245)

**Lines:** 228–245  
**Code:**
```js
if (!insertAfterCabOffer(container)) {
    var observerTimeout = setTimeout(function() {
        observer.disconnect();
    }, 5000);
    // ... observer watches for banner
}
```

**Problem:** If `#cab-promo-banner` never appears within 5 seconds, the observer disconnects and the widget is **never inserted anywhere**. The entire DOM structure (container, cards, styles) is built but never attached to the page. The user sees nothing — no error, no fallback.

**Solution:** Add a fallback insertion point when the timeout fires:
```js
var observerTimeout = setTimeout(function() {
    observer.disconnect();
    if (!inserted) {
        // Fallback: insert at a known safe location
        var fallback = document.querySelector(".booking-confirmation") 
                    || document.querySelector("main") 
                    || document.body;
        if (fallback) {
            fallback.appendChild(container);
            inserted = true;
        }
    }
}, 5000);
```

