### Issue 3: Styles Injected Even If Widget Is Never Inserted (Line 212)

**Line:** 212  
**Code:**
```js
document.head.appendChild(style);
```

**Problem:** The `<style>` block is appended to `<head>` unconditionally at line 212, before the insertion attempt at line 228. If `#cab-promo-banner` never appears and the widget is never inserted (see Issue 2), orphaned CSS rules remain in the document affecting page weight and potentially conflicting with other styles.

**Solution:** Move `document.head.appendChild(style)` inside the successful insertion path:
```js
function insertAfterCabOffer(cont) {
    if (inserted) return true;
    try {
        var target = document.querySelector("#cab-promo-banner");
        if (target && target.parentNode) {
            document.head.appendChild(style);  // inject styles only on success
            target.insertAdjacentElement("afterend", cont);
            inserted = true;
            return true;
        }
    } catch (e) {}
    return false;
}
```

