### Issue 5: Empty `titleHighlight` Span Serves No Purpose (Lines 111–113)

**Lines:** 111–113  
**Code:**
```js
var titleHighlight = document.createElement("span");
titleHighlight.className = "sew-title-highlight";
titleHighlight.textContent = "";
title.appendChild(titleHighlight);
```

**Problem:** An empty `<span>` is created and appended to the title. It renders nothing but adds a useless DOM node. If it's meant for future use (e.g., colored text portion), it should have content. As-is, it's dead code that could confuse maintainers when adapting this for other pages.

**Solution:** Either populate it with intended content or remove it:
```js
// If needed later:
titleHighlight.textContent = "— Hotels, Sightseeing & More";

// Or remove entirely:
// (delete lines 111–113)
```

