### Issue 7: Mobile Breakpoint Mismatch Between `<picture>` and CSS (Lines 19–20 vs 195)

**Lines:** 19–20 (picture sources) vs 195 (CSS media query)  
**Code:**
```js
// Picture element
sourceMobile.media = "(max-width: 768px)";   // 768px
sourceDesktop.media = "(min-width: 769px)";  // 769px

// CSS
"@media (max-width: 48rem) {"               // 48rem = 768px at default font-size
```

**Problem:** The `<picture>` breakpoint is at 768px, but the CSS layout switch uses `48rem`. If the user has a non-default root font-size (e.g., 18px), `48rem = 864px` — the mobile image will load at 768px but the mobile **layout** won't activate until 864px. This causes the mobile image to display inside the desktop grid layout, causing sizing/cropping issues.

**Solution:** Use the same unit consistently. Either use `px` in both:
```js
// CSS
"@media (max-width: 768px) {"
```
Or use `rem` in both (and update `<picture>` source media):
```js
sourceMobile.media = "(max-width: 48rem)";
sourceDesktop.media = "(min-width: 48.0625rem)";
```

